Global Lower Limb Exoskeleton Robot Market Insights
Lower Limb Exoskeleton Robot Market size was valued at USD 1.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.2 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 14.3% from 2024 to 2030.

Lower Limb Exoskeleton Robot Market Overview
The global lower limb exoskeleton robot market was valued at approximately USD 400 million in 2023 and is projected to expand at a CAGR of 35% from 2024 to 2032. This growth is driven by technological advancements, increasing demand for rehabilitation devices, and the need for improved mobility solutions. These exoskeletons are primarily used in healthcare settings for rehabilitation of individuals with lower-limb disabilities, but their applications are expanding to industrial and military sectors as well.

